# CarbonMirror – Environment Variables Example
#
# This file documents all configuration variables for the CarbonMirror platform.
# DO NOT put real API keys in this file – this file is committed to version control.
#
# Instructions:
#   1. Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored)
#   2. Fill in your actual values in .env
#   3. The application reads the Gemini API key at runtime via the in-app UI panel
#      (not from this file) to ensure keys are never persisted in source code.

# ─── GEMINI API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Your Google Gemini API key for the Decision Scanner feature.
# Obtain a key at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
#
# IMPORTANT: In the production application, this key is entered via the
# in-app header panel and stored ONLY in sessionStorage (ephemeral memory).
# It is NOT read from this file. This .env.example exists purely for
# documentation and CI/CD pipeline reference.
#
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ─── OPTIONAL: ANALYTICS (future integration) ─────────────────────────────────
#
# Optional privacy-respecting analytics endpoint (e.g., Plausible, Fathom).
# Leave blank if not using analytics.
#
# ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT=

# ─── OPTIONAL: APP METADATA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
APP_NAME=CarbonMirror
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
APP_ENV=development
